@node Main "Welcome to MathString"
@tab 30


  @{b}@{u}Welcome to MathString 1.5@{ub}@{uu}


  MathString is a @{" MUI " link MUI} custom class that adds mathematical abilities
to the usual String class.


  A MathString object can accept complex floating-point expression, including
algebraic operators, functions, measuring units and costants, returning only
the final result to the application.  It is highly customizable allowing for
different reactions on errors, custom functions, constants and measuring
units.



  @{u}Further information:@{uu}


  @{" Expression syntax " link SYNTAX}	What kind of expressions does MathString accept?

  @{" Programmers' info " link PROGINFO}	Where should I look for them?

  @{" Distribution conditions " link DISTRIB}	Can I use and distribute MathString?

  @{" Author " link AUTHOR}	How can I reach the author?



